<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1948&amp;p=11739#p11739"><![CDATA[
Hello all. Have not been to forum for awhile. Busy.<br /><br />Hello ZoNi. 20, 30, 50 % transparency!<br />I don't even know what the percentage relates to.<br />Is it log, exponential, or conversion of alpha ?/255 bits?<br />Which of the six types and is it for Win7 or 8?<br /><br />This is what I did, I made the skin as a quick reference to what plain transparencies looks like.<br /><br />Made a variation 1<br />I made the selectors and separators at 128/255 A<br />The main black part of menu at 216/255 A. I guess is around 15 %<br />The tops and bottoms at 235/255 A<br />A few edges at 250/255A.<br /><br />Variation 2 has main menu at 128/255 A. <br /><br />Variation 3 is 1/255 A.<br /><br />I put a transparency selection group in skin options, <br />so you, me or anybody can see what each does.<br /><br />Looks like alpha and glass, make the tops and bottom transparent, but not the main black menu.<br />Full alpha, and full glass make everything transparent.<br />Solid-transparent mixes to the background menu color. In this case white = grey.<br />Region seems to let the transparent edge dots show desktop, and block everything else, making a little darker. <br /><br />Here is where it gets weird.<br />Win7 <br />Fullalpha same <br />Fullglass same brightness as fullalpha, but with blur.<br /><br />Win8<br />Fullalpha same<br />Fullglass darker, no blur. <br /><br />I didn't give you exactly what you wanted.<br />Gave you the building blocks though.<br /><br />Every body has different tastes for see through menus. Also, might need to adjust the font smoothing, in CSM.<br />I see you like extreme. Just remember, white on dark desktop background looks great, <br />until a white window appears = whiteout <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_eek.gif" alt=":shock:" title="Shocked" /> <br /><br />ps. Skin file got kind of big. Over 1 meg. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sat Mar 29, 2014 7:01 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
